 blockade and contraband carriage. At the same time, neutral traders have done their best to evade and circumvent these restrictions. This book traces the evolution of state practice, together with the debates over the relevant doctrinal issues and the various attempts to reform and codify the law of neutrality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLAW / International.2bisacsh  aDeclaration of Paris.  aUN Charter.  abelligerents.  afree trade.  ainternational law.  alaws of naval warfare.  amaritime law.  aneutral traders.  aneutrality.1 aNeff, Stephen C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152617057640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526170576423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526170576/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles